Text: Qillqata (Aymara "qillqaña" to write, "-ta" a suffix to indicate the participle, "written" or "something written", hispanicized "Quelcata") is a mountain in the Wansu mountain range in the Andes of Peru, about 5000 m high.

Text: Qillqata (Condesuyos-La Unión):  Qillqata lies southeast of the mountain Pilluni, southwest of the mountain Janq'u Q'awa and east of the mountain Ch'uwañuma.
